  "text": "6:00 P.M. What does a predator call a hummingbird? Fast food! Sometimes nectar from flowers isn't enough to fill your tummy. Nectar gives you energy. but you get more protein. vitamins. and other nutrients from eating small insects and spiders. Can't find any flowers or bugs? You'll also snack on tree You have been known to eat sand. soil. and ash for their minerals. Your speed and precision make you a super hunter You can use your bill to grab insects out of midair and pluck them from spiderwebs. You're helpful to humans because you munch on insect pests like mosquitoes. fruit flies. mites. aphids. gnats. and wasps. You can consume anywhere from one to three times your body weight every day. While you're eating. you have to avoid predators. or creatures that prey upon hummingbirds. including snakes. bats. hawks. crows. squirrels. and toucans. Food BUSY'S YUMMY HUMMINGBIRD FOOD You and your friends love when humans put hummingbird feeders in their yards! an easy way to make hummingbird food. Combine fow parts water and one part white sugar in a pitcher or bowel. (So it you use cup of sugar. use cup of water.) Stir until the sugar is all dissolved Pour the mixture into a hummingbird feeder. Wait for us to fly by for a yummy meal! HummingbirdfoodshouldNOTincludereddyeor food coloring. It's not healthy and can actually be harmful. Besides, we love clear sugar water!",
